<item>
            <title>[FELIX-3231] Disable update counter</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-3231</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Update counter checks have been added to prevent multiple configuration updates with the same configuration in certain race condition situations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With the new R4.3 Configuration Admin (v1.4) it is now allowed that multiple ManagedService or ManagedServiceFactory services are registered with the same PID and that all receive the same configuration. This of course is incompatible with the current simple update counter mechanism.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For now we should just disable this check.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
